# Typography file workflow

Composite typography is **defined** in Token Studio JSON. In this repo, primitives/semantic colors in CSS are still hand-maintained; composite **definitions** live in JSON and are **generated to CSS** in the sibling **armada-poc** package.

## Source of truth (definitions)

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `src/tokens/armada-tokens.json` | **Edit composite definitions here** — `semantic.typography.*` |
| `src/styles/tokens.css` | Hand-maintained primitives/semantic colors (not auto-generated today) |
| `ARMADA_DESIGN_SYSTEM.md` | Human-readable composite table (keep in sync with JSON) |

## Generated CSS (armada-poc only)

Regeneration runs in **armada-poc**, not in this repo:

```bash
# From armada-poc repo root
npm run tokens:typography --workspace=@armada/ui
```

| Generated file (armada-poc) | Contents |
|-----------------------------|----------|
| `packages/ui/src/styles/typography.css` | `--semantic-typography-*` vars, `.armada-text-*` classes |
| `packages/ui/src/typography/variants.ts` | `TypographyVariant` type |

**Never hand-edit** those generated files in armada-poc. After changing `semantic.typography` in **this** repo’s `armada-tokens.json`, mirror the same change in armada-poc’s copy and run the command above.

